<item>
            <title>[DERBY-4410] NullPointerException when USING clause contains all columns in both join tables</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-4410</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;ij&amp;gt; create table t(x int);&lt;br/&gt;
0 rows inserted/updated/deleted&lt;br/&gt;
ij&amp;gt; select t1.&lt;b&gt;, t2.&lt;/b&gt; from t t1 join t t2 using &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/error.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;;&lt;br/&gt;
ERROR XJ001: Java exception: &apos;: java.lang.NullPointerException&apos;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This statement should have raised an exception because both t1.* and t2.* expand to no columns. See &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-4407&quot; title=&quot;StringIndexOutOfBoundsException in ij when result has no columns&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-4407&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-4407&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
